    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Blog-to-LinkedIn Converter\\n\",\"**NLP Project 47 of 100** — Rewrite a blog article into a LinkedIn post format.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import requests, re\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"BLOG = \\\"\\\"\\\"Machine Learning in 2025: What's Changed\\n\\nThe machine learning landscape has shifted dramatically. Traditional models are being replaced by foundation models. Fine-tuning is giving way to prompt engineering. And the tools are becoming accessible to non-engineers.\\n\\nKey trends:\\n1. LLMs are becoming commoditized - multiple providers offer comparable quality.\\n2. RAG has become the default architecture for enterprise AI.\\n3. Evaluation frameworks are finally catching up to model capabilities.\\n4. Small models are surprisingly competitive for focused tasks.\\n\\nThe bottom line? ML is no longer just for researchers. Product teams are building AI features directly.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\ndef blog_to_linkedin(blog_text, model='qwen3:1.7b'):\\n    prompt = f\\\"\\\"\\\"Convert this blog post into a LinkedIn post format:\\n- Start with a hook (first line should grab attention)\\n- Use short paragraphs and line breaks\\n- Add relevant emojis sparingly\\n- End with a question to drive engagement\\n- Keep under 200 words\\n\\nBlog:\\n{blog_text} /no_think\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    try:\\n        r = requests.post('http://localhost:11434/api/generate',json={'model':model,'prompt':prompt,'stream':False},timeout=60)\\n        return r.json().get('response','')\\n    except:\\n        # Rule-based fallback\\n        lines = blog_text.strip().split('\\\\n')\\n        hook = '🚀 ' + lines[0]\\n        body = '\\\\n\\\\n'.join(l.strip() for l in lines[1:] if l.strip())[:300]\\n        cta = '\\\\n\\\\nWhat\\\\'s the biggest ML shift you\\\\'ve noticed? 👇'\\n        return hook + '\\\\n\\\\n' + body + cta\\n\\nlinkedin_post = blog_to_linkedin(BLOG)\\nprint('=== LinkedIn Post ===')\\nprint(linkedin_post)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Blog-to-LinkedIn conversion changes format, tone, and length.**\\n\",\"- **LLMs handle the rewriting naturally** with proper prompts.\\n\",\"- **Rule-based fallback** works for basic formatting.\\n\",\"- **Key: hook, short paragraphs, emoji, CTA question.**\"]}\n",
